    <briefdescription>
<para>Represents an immutable snapshot of a SceneGraph at a given point in time. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>The class encapsulates all necessary data to render a single frame. It is designed to be a lightweight DTO to pass information to the rendering engine abstraction layer, such as the `RenderPass` class.</para>
<para>A snapshot includes a camera&apos;s projection and view matrix that should be used for rendering the scene. A collection of `SnapshotItems` holds the information about the renderable objects in the scene, preferably computed by using a `FrustumCullingStrategy` (<simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="classhelios_1_1scene_1_1Scene_1ab3ad742392c2a2b159cf8927ee6cf375" kindref="member">Scene::createSnapshot</ref>).</para>
</simplesect>
The class is not copyable to enforce its immutability and prevent unintended duplication of potentially large data sets. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
